messages.text: I understand Lyn is ‘helping’ you in some way?
I want you to leave my daughter alone!
She’s still dealing with physical and mental issues – from her fall.
I DO NOT want her involved in anymore of these problems at Munroe High!
I’ll keep her safe. I need her to
You should understand – with your own daughter, Sadie..
I think there’s going to be trouble here at the school, Mr. Danton!
Listen, Lyn, your mother wants you to
I overheard Makayla and Tamiko talking in the library this afternoon...
They were planning to meet back at school tonight – at eight...
It’s eight now, and I see a couple of bikes outside the school.
But I can’t get inside! The front doors are locked!
I’m in my car, on my way!
I’m picking up a text conversation! Here:
I found the nylon jump ropes in the phys-ed equipment room.
I’m bringing up the two small stepladders from the janitor’s room in the basement.
I’ll meet you in the gym.
Makayla and Tamiko are juniors at school, Mr. Danton!
They’re bullied because they’re shy and geeky...
hang around with each other so much.
They hate sports and gym class … I think?
The rear doors are locked, too! I can’t get in!
It’s the big rectangular building addition
with no windows at the back of the school!
Are you ready to be happy – forever? :-)
I have a rope and Tamiko has a rope.
We’re at opposite ends of the basketball court -
under the basketball hoops, with the stepladders.
and tie the loose ends of the ropes to the necks of the basketball hoops.
Then put the noosed ends of the ropes around your necks.
We just step off the ladder and..
You’ll get the last laugh on your haters..
When they find you in the morning at school.
Let’s wave at each other, one last time..
You crashed right through the gym doors with your car!!
Makayla’s going to be all right..
The paramedics are on their way.
We did all we could, Lyn.
I didn’t see you outside on the
I found a phone, Mr. Danton! In the parking lot!
I can almost feel an evil presence – out here in the dark..
Someone hit me on the side of the head.
Can you make it inside the gym!?
Get in here with me, Lyn! You’ll be safe!
I hear the ambulances! The paramedics will
I’m ok. Just a little woozy. %-)
How’s the school assembly going with all the parents?
I don’t want my daughter to have anymore involvement with you!
She’s recuperating at home. Her older sister is looking after her.
Why aren’t you here at the school to hear what the administrators have to say?
I would’ve thought with your own daughter and all, that
Sadie’s still in a coma. My wife’s at the hospital with her.
I’ve been driving the neighbourhood most of the night and today. Monitoring..
She has a nasty bump on her head!
No, I mean, do you think she could be mixed up in what happened to Sadie...
Mom tried to lock me up at home, but I snuck out. :o)
I’m here at school – way at the back of the theatre.
Mr. Slezak just started speaking to the parents and students..
And he just used the term: SUICIDE SOCIETY!!
Isn’t that what you told me GrimR texted you!?
The VP would have a key to the school...
and access to phys-ed and janitorial equipment.
THAT PSYCHO JUST SIGNED HIS OWN DEATH WARRANT
